	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Horses be soulbound.... or not</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=532439" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
I wanted to let everyone know about a small bug with the horses, that I, as awell as several other people, have experienced. The Horse Bridles you purchase in the Bazaar are intended to be soulbound to your character, like the Velious teeth and the Skyshrine key used to be. 
<P>
Unfortunately, due to a bug, they currently remain on your corpse. I have spoken to several GMs and they have confirmed that the bridle is supposed to remain on your character regardless of if you die, thus making the horses much more worth the cost you pay (ranging 10kpp - 130kpp+). Hopefully Verant will focus on patching this soon.
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=532439">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

